WEBVTT

00:08.492 --> 00:09.997
Previously on The Borgias...

00:10.009 --> 00:11.677
I would eliminate
the Sforza dynasty.

00:11.744 --> 00:13.445
Ludovico first.

00:13.479 --> 00:16.315
<i>He's in hiding</i>
<i>with Catherina's son, Benito.</i>

00:16.349 --> 00:18.750
I said "capture!"
Not "kill"!

00:19.819 --> 00:21.820
<i>What purchase can</i>
<i>we get with a dead Sforza?</i>

00:21.854 --> 00:23.221
Two dead Sforzas.

00:23.289 --> 00:26.458
Are you to be the one who
decides Rome's future?

00:26.492 --> 00:28.260
You followed me to Rome?

00:28.328 --> 00:29.895
Where does this
affection go?

00:29.963 --> 00:31.530
Affection leads
to weakness.

00:31.564 --> 00:33.165
<i>Sooner or later</i>
<i>he will tell you everything.</i>

00:33.232 --> 00:34.733
Remember the book.

00:34.801 --> 00:36.601
<i>Catallus's Carmina.</i>

00:36.669 --> 00:38.804
I have two cousins who
would fight to the death

00:38.838 --> 00:40.272
<i>for the throne of Naples,</i>

00:40.340 --> 00:42.341
<i>Prince Frederigo</i>
<i>and Prince Raphael.</i>

00:42.408 --> 00:44.843
<i>And I have no interest</i>

00:44.911 --> 00:46.445
in that kind of power!

00:46.546 --> 00:48.413
The Turk threatens our shipping.

00:48.514 --> 00:50.749
We will raise a mighty Crusade!

00:50.817 --> 00:54.953
The Crusade requires coin.
That is what he wants.

00:55.021 --> 00:56.989
The Spear of Longinus.

00:57.023 --> 00:58.890
<i>Pilgrims will</i>
<i>contribute generously</i>

00:58.925 --> 01:00.492
<i>to St. Peter's Pence.</i>

01:00.526 --> 01:03.362
We are putting on a show here.

01:04.897 --> 01:07.232
I accuse you of the poisoning
of the only barrier

01:07.266 --> 01:09.401
that lies between you
and the throne of Naples!

01:09.435 --> 01:11.403
<i>Hand the field over</i>
<i>to your brother!</i>

01:11.504 --> 01:12.971
So, we're safe now?

01:13.039 --> 01:16.041
As long as this king
lives, yes, we're safe.

01:16.075 --> 01:18.810
<i>I am Catherina</i>
<i>Sforza's eyes and ears,</i>

01:18.878 --> 01:21.613
<i>and I would beg you</i>
<i>to make no hasty moves</i>

01:21.714 --> 01:23.715
<i>until my exit is secured.</i>

01:23.750 --> 01:25.584
Bring me my copy of Catullus.

01:27.086 --> 01:30.729
[♪]

